UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304405X09001275
KW  - Conditional volatility
KW  - Model uncertainty
KW  - Disagreement
KW  - Factor models
AB  - We study asset pricing in economies featuring both risk and uncertainty. In our empirical analysis, we measure risk via return volatility and uncertainty via the degree of disagreement of professional forecasters, attributing different weights to each forecaster. We empirically model the typical risk-return trade-off and augment these models with our measure of uncertainty. We find stronger empirical evidence for an uncertainty-return trade-off than for the traditional risk-return trade-off. Finally, we investigate the performance of a two-factor model with risk and uncertainty in the cross section.
